\scriptsize
\texttt{raw} is the best AutoGluon permanent-CSI model on the 2016--2019 test set by AP and R@FPR5. \texttt{raw\_plus\_latent} is essentially tied on CV and has the best test-OOS AUC/R@FPR3, while \texttt{latent\_raw} performs best on test-OOS AP but remains weaker on CV/test AP.
\end{block}
\end{frame}

\begin{frame}{Appendix A14: Index Strategy Construction}
\scriptsize
\begin{columns}[T,onlytextwidth]
\begin{column}{0.50\textwidth}
\textbf{Strategy menu}
\begin{itemize}
  \item \textbf{Benchmark:} unfiltered market-cap-weighted index for each CRSP-like universe.
  \item \textbf{Temporary CSI:} \dyn{} score triggers finite exclusions; firms can re-enter after lockout expiry.
  \item Temporary thresholds: CV FPR $\leq 1\%$, CV FPR $\leq 3\%$, and Youden $J$.
  \item Temporary lockouts: 1, 2, 3, and 5 years; this gives 12 filtered strategies per universe.
  \item \textbf{Permanent CSI:} \perm{} score triggers absorbing removal after first active signal.
  \item Permanent thresholds: CV FPR $\leq 1\%$, CV FPR $\leq 3\%$, and Youden $J$; this gives 3 filtered strategies per universe.
\end{itemize}
\end{column}
\begin{column}{0.48\textwidth}
\textbf{Portfolio rule}
\vspace{-0.25em}
\begin{align*}
E_{i,t}^{temp} &= \mathbf{1}\{\hat p_{i,t}\geq \tau\}\times \mathbf{1}\{t \leq t_0 + L\},\\
E_{i,t}^{perm} &= \mathbf{1}\{\exists s\leq t: \hat p_{i,s}\geq \tau\},\\
w^{screen}_{i,t} &= \frac{(1-E_{i,t})MCAP_{i,t}}{\sum_{j\in U_t}(1-E_{j,t})MCAP_{j,t}}.
\end{align*}
\vspace{-0.7em}
\begin{itemize}
  \item Thresholds are calibrated from model validation/CV predictions, not from index OOS returns.
  \item Best-rule appendix rows select the highest annualized geometric return within each track, period, and universe.
  \item Error-cost decomposition reports annualized pp contributions from false positives, false negatives, true positives, and true negatives.
\end{itemize}
\end{column}
\end{columns}
% \sourcefoot{\texttt{11C\_IndexConstruction\_Revised.R}; \texttt{11c\_crsp\_index\_csi\_results\_20260516.md}.}
\end{frame}

